commentary: Shahid Afridi to Charles, OUT here comes the wicket! Here goes Lala with his arms spread out in self-praise. It was a flighted on, it drifted in and Charles was too early to jump out in a bid to smash it out of the ground. He gets beaten by the flight, beaten by the turn and beaten by the bounce. Easy meal for Afridi as Akmal flicks the bails off

commentary: Narine to Wahab Riaz, OUT Too good for Wahab, it has squeezed in from the little available space and has knocked the leg stump. That's wicket no. 3 for Narine! Wahab was shaping for the sweep, but is too late to bring his bat down to a quick missile fired in by Narine. The ball gets under his bat and pad before he can kneel down, strikes his stumps, the batsman slips and is left mourning on the floor
